And before she died, she actually saved hundreds

00:40:40.040 --> 00:40:41.040
of thousands of lives by speaking out in a
difficult community with so much prejudice

00:40:41.040 --> 00:40:42.040
against people living with HIV.
And she was able to use her power.

00:40:42.040 --> 00:40:43.040
So she's a champion.
The Global Fund, the Gates organization, the

00:40:43.040 --> 00:40:44.040
government -- they're all champions.
And this is a picture of Michael Holscher,

00:40:44.040 --> 00:40:45.040
who originally approached me to do this.
And so, for me, he's a champion.

00:40:45.040 --> 00:40:46.040
And I think that, that's really my point -- that
everybody has it in them, and everybody can

00:40:46.040 --> 00:40:47.040
be a champion.
These are some of our Celebrity Ambassadors.

00:40:47.040 --> 00:40:48.040
We try to find culturally relevant ways to
work with different people from different

00:40:48.040 --> 00:40:49.040
backgrounds to get different messages out.
And these are just some of the people.

00:40:49.040 --> 00:40:50.040
Miss Universe, Bono, Ashley Judd, Juanas,
and this gentleman who is our ambassador.

00:40:50.040 --> 00:40:51.040
His name is Akshay Kumar in India, because
